    <decisions>
      <decision id="D1" name="Feature-flag handling">
        Chose Option A (delete entirely) per task brief recommendation. Rationale: kill-switch
        for universal-ingest now lives at the playbook-deployment layer (deploy a no-op
        Dataverse playbook to disable). This survives BFF redeploys and matches the same
        mechanism predict-matter-cost@v1 uses. Eliminates Tier-1.5-anti-pattern surface
        area in BFF DI config.
      </decision>
      <decision id="D2" name="EventId disposition">
        <event id="8060" name="InsightsRunIngestRoutedToPlaybook">DELETED — always taken now; pure noise.</event>
        <event id="8061" name="InsightsRunIngestRoutedToLegacy">DELETED — no legacy path remains.</event>
        <event id="8062" name="InsightsRunIngestPlaybookAdapterMismatch">KEPT — still defensive (e.g., sanitize short-circuit).</event>
        <event id="8063" name="InsightsRunIngestPlaybookFailed">KEPT — reworded from "falling back" to "failure propagates per ADR-004".</event>
      </decision>
      <decision id="D3" name="Per-env playbook Guid resolution">
        Inject IOptionsMonitor&lt;InsightsPlaybookNameMapOptions&gt; (the existing per-env
        name→Guid map used by /api/insights/ask for predict-matter-cost@v1). Canonical
        name = "universal_ingest_v1" (snake_case_only per POSIX env-var rules; see
        InsightsPlaybookNameMapOptions XML doc). Empty-Guid response throws
        InvalidOperationException with actionable error message naming the missing config key.
      </decision>
    </decisions>

